--- !u!114 &1837174047
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1837174045}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 7e2d3ed8a5dcd1a4a97f685a000bc6bb, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ToturialScreen
  contentText: {fileID: 439706908}
  closeButton: {fileID: 1609993405}
  previousButton: {fileID: 1161387611}
  nextButton: {fileID: 2007750245}
  screenRoot: {fileID: 1837174045}
  pages:
  - content: "1. Game Objective\n\nThe core gameplay of FetchVR is playing fetch
      with your dog.\n\nWhat you do:\nThrow the ball\nCommand the dog to fetch it\nWait
      for the dog to bring it back\nRepeat the next round\n\nAdditionally, when the
      dog\u2019s Satiety, Training, and Mood stats all reach their maximum, the dog
      will level up and become smarter."
  - content: '2. VR Controller Input


      The main gameplay only uses three inputs
      from the right hand:


      Trigger: Throw the ball

      Primary Button:
      Command the dog to fetch

      Secondary Button: Reset the current round

      Grab:
      Pick up the ball or pet the dog


      If the round gets stuck or you want
      to restart, press the secondary button.'
  - content: '3. Throwing Mechanics


      Throwing is based on the orientation
      and movement speed of your right-hand controller.


      This means:


      The
      ball travels in the direction your controller is pointing

      More natural
      arm movement results in more realistic throws

      Simply tapping the trigger
      may result in poor throws


      For best results: aim first, then perform
      a natural forward throwing motion while pressing the trigger.'
  - content: '4. Interaction System


      Besides playing fetch, you can also interact
      with your dog:


      Petting: Aim at the dog to trigger petting, which increases
      mood

      Feeding: Use the controller ray to click the feeding button in
      the scene, which increases satiety


      This makes the game not just about
      training, but also about companionship and bonding.'
  startingPageIndex: 0
  currentPageIndex: 0
